data.name: HTTPSCheckbox.ToolTip2
data.value: This should be ticked unless you are really not going to deploy a HTTPS site. When this is ticked the authentication cookie will require HTTPS, the RequireHttps filter will be applyed to all requests and the Strict-Transport-Security header will be added. When this is not ticked you will have to add all this your self if you then need it.

data.name: AdminUserPasswordTextbox.ToolTip
data.value: The password that the admin user will use to login to the website. As the admin user is likly to have the highest level of permissions this should be complex and difficult to guess. This can be empty but this really should not be done.

data.name: AdminUserUsernameTextbox.ToolTip
data.value: The username that the admin user will use to login to the website. Tipically you will need an admin user to manage users and other aspects of your system if not just to create the first real user. You should have a username that is not easy to guess so it is not advised to have this be Admin, Administrator or any thing easy to work out.
